National Super League leaders, APS Bomet will be out to consolidate their position at the apex of the second tier log when they face Naivas at the IAAF Stadium in Bomet this afternoon. APS have amassed 61 points thus far, six clear of their closest challengers Muhoroni Youth. Naivas are fourth with 49 points. Muhoroni Youth who are keen on a return to top flight football after a decade in the cold face SS Assad at the Shamu Grounds, Ukunda. Whereas Muhoroni have 54 points, Assad are 15th with 35. Coastal Heroes will hope to shake off their relegation woes when they host Mara Sugar at Mbaraki Sports Club. The coastal lads are second from the bottom with 25 points. Mara are 11th with 37. Fortune Sacco will look to reignite tgeir promotion hopes when they settle scores with Mombasa Elite at Kianyaga Stadium. Fortune are currently third on the log with 54 points while Elite are eighth with 44. Silibwet take on former Kenyan Premier League side Kisumu All Stars at the IAAF Stadium in Bomet. Although both sides have 35 points, Kisumu are 14th while Silibwet are 16th on goal difference. Gusii United host Dandora Love at the Green Stadium in Awendo. Gusii are currently 17th with 28 points while Dandora are at the bottom with 20 points. Vihiga and Shabana renew rivalry at the Mumias Complex as Mwatate and Murangâ€™a SEAL face off at Wundanyi Stadium. Editing by Tony Mballa